"Streetwalker" starts with a bold sound like 60s vocal pop hits with its drum intro bearing resemblance to "Be My Baby" by "The Ronettes." It maintains that 60s vibe in its chorus with strumming guitars all the while maintaining a full alternative sound. The song sounds happy but the lyrics highlight the serious topic of human trafficking.

> Oh Lord, set them free, set them free\
It could have been me

