### History From Below (2010)

#### Track 2 - Bushwick Blues

{% Player
   trackId="0xV0YnO4o2D6vsj4OrFuxY"
   trackArtist="Delta Spirit"
   trackName="Bushwick Blues"
   trackAlbumArt="delta-spirit-history-from-below-2010"
   platformLinks={spotify: "https://open.spotify.com/track/0xV0YnO4o2D6vsj4OrFuxY", youtube: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gcvUjAR2vR8", deezer: "https://music.apple.com/us/song/bushwick-blues/1443137632", bandcamp: "https://link.deezer.com/s/333xbE34QGg3jrABivsTq", soundcloud: "https://soundcloud.com/deltaspirit/bushwick-blues?in=deltaspirit/sets/history-from-below&si=21a0d8f87d814d4590f056eb43b20b87"} /%}

Also worth listening is the acoustic folksy [Live (Waits Room Version)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VahmtKS9B7g)&nbsp;of "Bushwick Blues." With this song we see the band stray away a bit from its country origins and while the song still has some of those elements it's more indie rock now. Nonetheless it has the same "Delta Spirit" passion in playing and singing. The energetic playing gives the song a real emotional quality especially with lyrics about loving someone so much you can't forget them no matter how hard you try to move on. The way he delays saying "after all" in the lyrics has a wonderful sadness to it.

> Because my love is strong\
And my heart is weak after all

