### Delta Spirit (2012)

#### Track 3 - California

{% Player
   trackId="4Y3gLYlV5rD3fhirhWKtei"
   trackArtist="Delta Spirit"
   trackName="California"
   trackAlbumArt="delta-spirit-self-titled-2012"
   platformLinks={spotify: "https://open.spotify.com/track/4Y3gLYlV5rD3fhirhWKtei", youtube: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Va0ezWC2du4", appleMusic: "https://music.apple.com/us/song/california/1443140597", deezer: "https://link.deezer.com/s/333xe1q4VMk4ISWQjvOZ2", soundcloud: "https://soundcloud.com/deltaspirit/california-1?si=ea6c0037ad234a4e91cc9d74788b3d05"} /%}

{% Iframe
   code="<iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Va0ezWC2du4?rel=0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>" /%}

"California" is another indie track but with the quality lyricism expected of "Delta Spirit". "California" is very tame, compared to their other songs, only packing a punch with it's lyric-less chorus. The focus in this song are its heartbreaking lyrics of self-sacrifice in the face of inadequacy. It's about recognizing a love that can never be. The reverberating guitars sound as if they're almost crying to the words.

> I want you to wander silent past my outstretched arms\
I want you to hide yourself from all I see\
And though my heart will fight until its dying breath, you’re not for me

